From: pai-nix <pai-nix@localhost>
Date: Sun, 3 May 2026 15:35:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 11/11] Substitute {{...}} placeholders in PAI_SYSTEM_PROMPT.md

Upstream issue: danielmiessler/Personal_AI_Infrastructure#1135

PAI/PAI_SYSTEM_PROMPT.md ships with 25 unresolved placeholders:
  {{PRINCIPAL_NAME}} ×17
  {{DA_NAME}}        ×7
  {{DA_FULL_NAME}}   ×1

The TS installer at PAI/PAI-Install/engine/actions.ts substitutes
identity into CLAUDE.md, DA_IDENTITY.md, and PRINCIPAL_IDENTITY.md
(handlers near line 1430). The constitutional system prompt
PAI_SYSTEM_PROMPT.md is NOT touched. Result: every session boots
with the system prompt addressing the model as `{{DA_FULL_NAME}}`
instead of the chosen DA name, and "{{PRINCIPAL_NAME}}" instead of
the user's name. The token literals reach the model verbatim.

Token-format note: PAI_SYSTEM_PROMPT.md uses double-brace flat tokens
({{DA_NAME}}, {{PRINCIPAL_NAME}}). CLAUDE.md uses single-brace dotted
tokens ({DA_IDENTITY.NAME}, {PRINCIPAL.NAME}). Different syntax,
different consumers — this patch handles only the double-brace form
in the named file.

Backtick preservation: line 37 contains a doctrine example showing
the literal output-template format:

  Final visible token is the mode's closing line (`🗣️ {{DA_NAME}}: …`
  or the Algorithm `━━━ 📃 SUMMARY ━━━ 7/7` block).

This {{DA_NAME}} is inside a single-backtick code span and must stay
literal so future readers see it as a generic placeholder, not as
their specific DA's name. The patch substitutes only outside
single-backtick spans (split-by-`/(`[^`\n]*`)/g`/, even-index chunks).

Live count on upstream: 25 placeholders, 1 preserved (line 37 inside
backticks), 24 substituted.

Files touched (paths relative to upstream source root):

  Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/PAI/PAI-Install/engine/actions.ts          :1477+
    Adds a 22-line PAI_SYSTEM_PROMPT.md handler block after the
    PRINCIPAL_IDENTITY.md handler, before the .env API keys block.

Total: 1 file, 1 hunk. Net +22 lines added.

Co-existence: patches 0008/0009/0010 modify actions.ts at lines 14,
1043, 1244, 1396, 1530 — all non-overlapping with this patch's
target at line ~1477. Hunks generated via diff -u against the
post-0010 result/ tree.

Verified via synthetic substitution: aiName="Val",
principalName="Klemen" produces "Val — Personal AI" 1×, 7× "Val"
total (1 from DA_FULL_NAME + 6 from DA_NAME outside backticks),
17× "Klemen", and the 1 backtick-protected {{DA_NAME}} remains
literal.
---
--- a/Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/PAI/PAI-Install/engine/actions.ts
+++ b/Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/PAI/PAI-Install/engine/actions.ts
@@ -1475,6 +1475,28 @@
     } catch {}
   }
 
+  // PAI_SYSTEM_PROMPT.md — uses double-brace tokens (different from CLAUDE.md's
+  // single-brace dotted tokens). Substitute {{DA_NAME}} / {{DA_FULL_NAME}} /
+  // {{PRINCIPAL_NAME}} OUTSIDE single-backtick spans. Backtick spans contain
+  // doctrine examples (e.g. `🗣️ {{DA_NAME}}: …` showing the output template
+  // format) that must stay literal so users reading the prompt see them as
+  // the generic placeholder, not their own DA's name.
+  const systemPromptPath = join(paiDir, "PAI", "PAI_SYSTEM_PROMPT.md");
+  if (existsSync(systemPromptPath)) {
+    try {
+      const daFullName = `${aiName} — Personal AI`;
+      const content = readFileSync(systemPromptPath, "utf-8");
+      const rendered = content.split(/(`[^`\n]*`)/g).map((seg, i) => {
+        if (i % 2 === 1) return seg;
+        return seg
+          .replace(/\{\{DA_FULL_NAME\}\}/g, daFullName)
+          .replace(/\{\{DA_NAME\}\}/g, aiName)
+          .replace(/\{\{PRINCIPAL_NAME\}\}/g, principalName);
+      }).join("");
+      writeFileSync(systemPromptPath, rendered);
+    } catch {}
+  }
+
   // Create .env file for API keys
   await emit({ event: "progress", step: "configuration", percent: 50, detail: "Setting up API keys..." });
 
